---
description: Enforce 4pt grid for UI styling with 1px exception
alwaysApply: true
---

# UI Spacing: Multiples of 4

Use values that are multiples of 4 for UI styling measurements by default.

Apply this to spacing and sizing values, including:
- padding and margin
- gaps and offsets
- width and height
- corner radius
- icon and touch target sizes

Allowed exception:
- use single-pixel values when a true 1px component is needed (for example: borders, dividers, hairlines, or 1px separators)

Examples:

```swift
// ✅ Good
.padding(16)
.cornerRadius(12)
.frame(width: 48, height: 48)

// ✅ Allowed 1px exception
.overlay(Rectangle().frame(height: 1))

// ❌ Avoid
.padding(10)
.cornerRadius(7)
```
